. Two strings A and B are called anagrams if it is possible to make A and B equal by rearranging characters of A and B. This means abcd and dcab are anagrams while abc and bcd is not

Input Format

The first line contains an integer, N, denoting the size of the string S. The next line contains an integer, M. denoting the size of the string The next line contains a string, S, denoting the string S The next line contains a string, T, denoting the string T

Constraints

1<= â„– <= 10^5

1-14 <= 100

1< len(S) <= 10:5
